examples.en: The latest news threatens trouble for the economy.
The practice threatens to become general.
Poaching threatens the survival of the rhino.
The incident threatens to scuttle the peace process.
Overfishing threatens the survival of certain fish species.
This new leader meanly threatens the deepest values of our society.
A blatant, insolent materialism threatens to engulf moral distinctions.
In The Odyssey, Ulysses is trapped between the six-headed monster Scylla and Charybdis, a deadly whirlpool that threatens to suck in his ship.
The incident threatens to ruin his chances in the election.
